title: No. 6 LSU holds off No. 8 Florida, 35-28 (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,338 No. 6 LSU holds off No. 8 Florida, 35-28 (Yahoo Sports) Perhaps someone at Florida should have reminded first-year coach Jim McElwain about Les Miles' propensity to gamble against the Gators. Leonard Fournette ran for 180 yards and two touchdowns, Miles victimized Florida with a fake field goal for the second time in five years, and the No. 6 Tigers beat the No. 8 Gators 35-28 on Saturday night.
